The South African Weather Service (Saws) has once again warned KwaZulu-Natal residents of scattered showers and thundershowers expected over the western and southern parts of KZN on Thursday afternoon. The weather office said some of these thunderstorms are expected to become severe producing heavy downpours, strong damaging winds, hail and excessive lightning. The areas that are expected to be affected include Abaqulusi, Alfred Duma - Indaka, Alfred Duma - Ladysmith, Dannhauser, Dr N. Dlamini-Zuma - Underberg, eDumbe, eMadlangeni, Endumeni, Greater Kokstad, Impendle, Ingwe, Inkosi Langalibalele - Estcourt, Inkosi Langalibalele - Sobabili, Mkhambathini, Mpofana - Giants Castle, Mpofana - Mooi River, Msinga, Newcastle, Nquthu, Okhahlamba, Richmond, Msunduzi, Ubuhlebezwe, uMngeni, uMshwathi, UMuziwabantu, Umvoti and Umzimkhulu. People are urged to stay indoors during the storm, if outdoors, seek shelter immediately but not under trees, telephone and power lines. People are advised to take caution or avoid travelling on bridges and roads in low lying areas as these may be susceptible to flooding and there may be sinkholes.